# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
So the Idea behind this approach is :
- First we gonna talk about Brute force that will be done by using three loops checking every triplet and if any triplet satisfy the condtion we gonna return true. (But --> $$O(N^3)$$😔)
- Second little better brute force that can be checking using two loops only whether  
    - checking frist two two elemnts through i and jth loop and third can be chekced from a map which stores elemnts one by one from back and we have to check if arr[i]<arr[j] and maps biggest elemnt >arr[i] and <arr[j] . 
    - Or we can have a mini variable  in ith loop (i.e left hand side) and we check  arr[i]<arr[j] and arr[i]>mini beacsue mini is in front so we can do this using two loops.

- **Now coming to the beast O(N)**:
- So the idea behind that appraoch is since traversing from back will be more handy in this case so try to imagine that way . If we somehow can check what gonna be our arr[k] our work is done because then we have to only find a number less than it and our answer will be true. That is because if we take an example e.g 9 3 6 5 4 3
- so here traversing from back side first we will take 3 but we are not confirm if it gonna be our arr[k] , but we take so after we check if some elemnt is greater than it if yes we gonna now need only arr[i] now if our arr[k]>arr[i] we gonna return true so 
- take 3 i.e arr[k] now 4 is greter than 3 i.e arr[j] so now 5 but want less than 3 we can't find so the thing is we are not sure of selecting arr[k] , arr[j] can be biggest in array and arr[i] can smallest in array but not sure about arr[k] so we somehow have to first take and untake that after some condition so we are gonna use **stack** beacuse we can pop earlier values and focus on new .That was the idea why we will use stack
- So the idea is first initialze **kth with INT_MIN** then start the loop from back and check if current element is less than k return true else check in stack if st.top is lesser than curr it can be taken as arr[j] and rest all will be popped and top can be taken as k and also keep pushing the elements in stack at the end as well. Now if next elemnt is less than k return true or if not check if its bigger than st.top again pop elemnts and take kth  as st.top.
-  we are doing this beacuse we want the kth element  lesser than jth but enough bigger tha ith . So once an element is less than kth we will return true.
- Also if we observe on thing until some elemnt is not bigger than our st.top our k will not be intilaized until that
-  so in this way in the given example first our k is 3 then 4 then 5 then 3 will come which less than 5 so will return true .
