Hllo there , so in this we are making 3 data stores :-
**1. SET** :-  to store the distinct values  from left to the point where we are currently there
**2. MAP** :- to simply store the count of every number 
**3. MINV** :- to simply store the minimum   number  from the point where we are from starting (i.e. on the left)
**UPPER BOUND function is a gift to all of us as it simply returns the just upper value in the given set** .
While traversing the array we see that if the just above value of the minv in the right hand side is smaller than current value or not : if yes then return true else move to next  and remove the current value of its count is 0 . *(read it again)* 
FOR EX :- 
