# Approach
1. We create an increasing order stack (from top to bottom) traversing from back of the array.
2. If nums[i] is less than top of stack then we simply push it into the stack maintining its monotonicity. 
3. If nums[i] is greater than the stack, then this could be our possible contender for J. 
4. We find out the number just smaller than nums[i] in the stack. This will act as our K. And push nums[i] into the stack.
4. Now if at any point if nums[i] < K then we know that, there exist a value greater than K in the stack and now we have a value lesser than K. So we have our triplet. 

