Simple logic, readable variables. It's not to compete who writes the less lines of code....also confusing variable naming is very bad, which will waste the reader lots of time to understand the problem.

Logic
1.  define data structure:   int a2, stack a3 and try to find a1.
2.  iterate from the end to start, the stack always has the largest number from the current position. So we only need to find the condition that a1 < a2, and a3 is for storing the largest number.

```
class Solution {
    public boolean find132pattern(int[] nums) {
        if(nums == null  || nums.length <= 2) return false;
        Stack<Integer> a3Stack = new Stack<>();

        int a2 = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int i = nums.length-1; i >= 0; i--) {
	    	// current nums[i] could be the candidate of (a1,a3), that's depends on the comparation of a2
            if(nums[i] > a2) { // nums[i] is a candidate of a3.
			    // fine the largest possible value of a2.
                while(!a3Stack.isEmpty() && nums[i] > a3Stack.peek()) {
                    a2 = a3Stack.pop();
                }
                // push the current largest number in the a3Stack.
                a3Stack.push(nums[i]);
            } else if(nums[i] == a2) {
                continue;
            } else {
                //nums[i] < a2; nums[i] is a1 at this moment.
                return true;
            }

        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

